phase2.explanation:
You used a variable in `Update()` that was never initialized.

**The fix:**
```csharp
private Rigidbody rb;

void Start()
{
    rb = GetComponent<Rigidbody>();  // ← Initialize here!
}

void Update()
{
    if (rb != null)
    {
        rb.AddForce(Vector3.up * 10);
    }
}
```

**Sharp-chan says:**
"Always check if your references are set before using them. `Start()` is the perfect place to set them up."
